The '''Decree of Aristoteles''' was a decree passed by the [[Athenian Assembly]] in February or March 377 BC.{{sfn|Hamilton|1980|p=83}} The decree is preserved as the inscription on a [[stele]]; this is the most important [[epigraphy|epigraphical source]] for the [[Second Athenian Confederacy]].{{sfn|Baron|2006|p=379}} The decree, often known as the "'''Charter of the Second Athenian Confederacy'''", formalised earlier Athenian diplomacy inviting states to join Athens and her allies in a permanent alliance.{{sfn|Hamilton|1980|p=83}} The inscription of the decree was first published in 1852,{{sfn|Baron|2006|p=383}} and it has received much attention from scholars since then.{{sfn|Baron|2006|p=379}}

